[src:avl-tree/binary-search-tree] If ${\text{Y}}$ lies within ${\text{Z}}$ 's right subtree but is not ${\text{Z}}$ 's right child, as shown in (e), ${\text{Y}}$ first gets replaced by its own right child, and then it displaces ${\text{Z}}$ 's position in the tree.
[src:avl-tree/binary-search-tree] Alternatively, the in-order predecessor can also be used.
